) does not want you reading this. It would prefer you scroll through your phone, pour another drink, or convince yourself you will \u8220"start Monday.\u8221" The fact that you are still reading means some part of you\u8221"\u8221"the part we call the Operator\u8221"\u8221"is still fighting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let us honor that fight by giving you a clear path forward.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b WHAT YOU NEED}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Before you continue, gather these items:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b A notebook} \u8220"\u8221" This will become your Field Journal. It does not need to be fancy. A $3 spiral notebook works. A leather journal works. What matters is that it is {\i yours alone} and you will not lose it.\par}
