{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 CHAPTER 7: RADAR CALIBRATION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b (MINDFULNESS & THE VOID)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In a world of constant noise, Silence is a tool.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you look around, you will notice that modern humans are uncomfortable with silence.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab We play podcasts in the car.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab We listen to music in the gym.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab We have the TV on in the background.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab We scroll our phones on the toilet.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Why? Because {\b The Passenger is uncomfortable with stillness.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Silence forces you to notice the hull damage. Silence forces you to hear the engine rattling. Silence brings up the thoughts you are trying to avoid\u8212-the regrets, the fears, the grief.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 So the Passenger fills the airspace with constant noise. It creates a wall of sound to keep you from hearing your own inner voice.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b ENTERING THE VOID}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Operator enters the Void willingly.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We practice {\b Mindfulness}, which is a gentle word for a powerful skill: {\b Radar Calibration.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Mindfulness is simply the ability to see what is happening {\i while} it is happening.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Most people only realize they are angry {\i after} they have said something they regret.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Most people only realize they are stressed {\i after} they have eaten the whole container.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Operator notices they are getting angry {\i while} the anger is rising. This moment of awareness is the difference between a Reaction (Passenger) and a Response (Operator).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE SCIENCE OF THE SCAN (DMN Deactivation)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ancient traditions call this \u8220"mindfulness.\u8221" Neuroscientifically, they are describing the same thing: {\b Deactivation of the Default Mode Network (DMN).}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The DMN is the brain network active when you are daydreaming, worrying about the future, or regretting the past. It is the home of the Passenger\u8217's running commentary.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When you actively check your state (\u8220"Am I angry? Am I tired? What is happening in my body right now?\u8221"), you physically power down the DMN and activate the {\b Task-Positive Network (TPN).}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You cannot be lost in the story {\i and} observing the story at the same time. The act of checking switches the neural tracks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b CASE BRIEF: THE DRIFT}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Scenario:} You are driving home from work. You had a hard day. Traffic is heavy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Drift:} The Passenger is murmuring: \u8220"I hate this job. My back hurts. I deserve a treat. I will stop and get [the thing].\u8221" You are on Autopilot.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Radar Ping:} You trigger a mental checkpoint. \u8220"STATUS REPORT.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Scan:} You realize your jaw is clenched. Your breathing is shallow. You are feeling {\i resentment.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Correction:} Because you spotted the pattern miles before the decision point, you can steer around it. You drive home instead of stopping. You take a walk instead of numbing.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Without the radar, you would have arrived at the destination before you even knew you were heading there.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE S.I.T.R.E.P. DRILL}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When you feel the pressure rising\u8212-when the chest gets tight, or the craving hits, or the irritation builds\u8212-you do not react. You execute a {\b SITREP} (Situation Report).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b STOP:} Pause the body. Put down whatever is in your hands. Close your mouth.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b INHALE:} Execute a Box Breath. (4 seconds In, 4 seconds Hold, 4 seconds Out, 4 seconds Hold).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Why:} This physically activates the Vagus Nerve and lowers your heart rate. You cannot be in panic mode and deep breathing mode at the same time.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b TENSION:} Check your body. Drop your shoulders. Unclench your jaw.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab {\b REPORT:} Ask the question: {\i \u8220"What is the actual situation?\u8221"}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Passenger:} \u8220"I need [the thing].\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\i Operator:} \u8220"I am feeling anxious because of the email. The thing will not fix the email. It will only numb the sensor.\u8221"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab {\b EXECUTE:} Name the next right action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab {\b PROCEED:} Take that action.\sa180\par}
