{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE BEDROOM DOCTRINE}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The bedroom is a special case. It serves two purposes: sleep and intimacy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It should serve nothing else.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Problem:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you work in bed, the brain begins to associate \u8220"bed\u8221" with \u8220"work.\u8221" If you scroll in bed, the brain associates \u8220"bed\u8221" with \u8220"stimulation.\u8221" This leads to insomnia.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Protocol:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No screens in bed (ideally no screens in the bedroom at all)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab No work in bed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If you cannot sleep after 20 minutes, get up and sit in another space until drowsy, then return\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Passenger should learn: {\i \u8220"Bed means sleep.\u8221"} Nothing else.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b CASE BRIEF: THE FRIDGE PLACEMENT}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Scenario:} You walk into the kitchen. You open the fridge. You eat something you did not intend to eat.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Problem:} The fridge is at eye level, always visible, always easy. Every time you walk by, the Passenger notices it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Solutions:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Stock visually:} Put healthy options at eye level. Put indulgent options behind barriers (in opaque containers, in the back).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b The fruit bowl principle:} A visible fruit bowl increases fruit consumption. A visible cookie jar increases cookie consumption. What you see, you eat.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Inconvenience as tool:} If you struggle with snacking, require that you sit at a table to eat. No eating standing at the fridge.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You are not weak for eating what is easy. You are human. Design for the human you are, not the robot you wish you were.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
