{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 CHAPTER 16: DAMAGE CONTROL\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b (RELAPSE & THE SHAME SPIRAL)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You will make mistakes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Despite everything you have learned, despite your best intentions, there will come a day when the Passenger seizes the wheel and you do the thing you swore you would not do.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This chapter is about what happens next.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE INEVITABILITY OF VARIANCE}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you are trying to change a deeply ingrained pattern\u8212-addiction, compulsion, self-sabotage\u8212-perfection is not realistic.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The question is not \u8220"Will I slip?\u8221" The question is \u8220"What will I do when I slip?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Critical Window:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The moments after a slip are the most dangerous. Not because of the slip itself, but because of what the Passenger does with it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Passenger will try to turn a lapse into a collapse.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE ABSTINENCE VIOLATION EFFECT}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Psychologists Alan Marlatt and Judith Gordon identified a pattern called the {\b Abstinence Violation Effect (AVE)}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Here is how it works:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab You commit to a goal (sobriety, clean eating, no scrolling)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab You slip (one drink, one binge, one scroll session)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab The Passenger initiates two responses:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Attribution:} \u8220"This happened because I am fundamentally broken. I have no willpower. I knew I could not do this.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab {\b Catastrophizing:} \u8220"I already blew it. The day/week/attempt is ruined. I might as well go all the way.\u8221"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab The slip becomes a binge. The binge confirms the attribution. The shame deepens.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The AVE is the real enemy\u8212-not the slip itself.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A single drink does not derail recovery. The belief that \u8220"I already failed, so I might as well keep going\u8221" derails recovery.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b THE OPERATOR\u8217'S RESPONSE TO A SLIP}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When the slip happens:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Step 1: STOP}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Physically pause. Put down or step away from whatever you are doing. Do not continue on autopilot.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Step 2: Reframe}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Passenger is screaming: \u8220"You failed. You are weak. You are back to zero.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Operator responds: \u8220"I had a slip. A slip is not a relapse. The next decision is still mine.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b A slip is an event. A relapse is a pattern.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You are not at zero. Every day of practice before the slip still counts. The neural pathways you have been building are still there.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Step 3: Contain}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The goal now is {\b Damage Control.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Do not attempt to \u8220"make up for it\u8221" by doing something extreme. Do not punish yourself. The goal is simply to stop the bleeding and return to baseline as quickly as possible.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab One cookie is a slip. Eating the whole box is the AVE.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab One drink is a slip. Staying at the bar is the AVE.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Missing one gym session is a slip. Canceling the membership is the AVE.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Stop the cascade.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Step 4: Log}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Open your Field Journal. Write:\par}
