{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b 4. Titration}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Titration\u8221" means approaching trauma in small, manageable doses rather than flooding. This is a professional skill, but the principle applies to self-help: You do not need to \u8220"fully feel\u8221" everything all at once. Small, contained doses of processing, followed by stabilization.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b CASE BRIEF: THE INEXPLICABLE REACTION}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Scenario:} Your partner raises their voice during an argument. You freeze. You cannot speak. Later, you feel rageful or numb for hours.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b What happened:} The raised voice triggered a trauma memory\u8212-possibly from childhood, possibly from a past relationship. Your nervous system went into survival mode (freeze), then could not fully return to baseline.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Passenger\u8217's interpretation:} \u8220"I am crazy. I overreact to everything. Something is wrong with me.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Operator\u8217's reframe:} \u8220"My nervous system is responding to old data. The reaction makes sense given my history. This is a signal that there is unprocessed material.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The path forward:} This is not about \u8220"controlling yourself\u8221" in the moment. This is about healing the underlying alarm system. That requires dedicated work\u8212-likely with professional support.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b A NOTE ON COMPLEX TRAUMA (C-PTSD)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some trauma is not a single event. It is a chronic condition\u8212-years of abuse, neglect, or instability, often in childhood.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is called {\b Complex Trauma} or {\b C-PTSD} (Complex PTSD).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It is characterized by:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pervasive shame and worthlessness\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Difficulty regulating emotions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Relationship difficulties (attachment issues)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Dissociation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Loss of core beliefs and meaning\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If this describes you, please know:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab You are not broken. Your system adapted to survive impossible conditions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Healing is possible, but it is slow. Expect years, not months.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Specialized treatment is important\u8212-not just any therapy, but trauma-informed therapy.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Community can help. Support groups for survivors provide connection with others who understand.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b OPERATOR\u8217'S NOTES \u8212- CHAPTER 18}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trauma is a nervous system event, not a character flaw\u8212-it is a survival response that got stuck\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trauma is stored in the body; you cannot think your way out of it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The Window of Tolerance shrinks with trauma\u8212-the goal is gradual expansion\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Triggers are not weakness; they are signals of unprocessed material\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Self-sabotage often has trauma roots: dysregulation, self-medication, repetition compulsion\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Healing from complex trauma is possible, but it is slow\u8212-expect years, not months\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b OPERATOR\u8217'S ORDERS \u8212- CHAPTER 18}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Professional support is typically necessary: TF-CBT, EMDR, somatic therapy, IFS.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab You can begin now: regulate the nervous system, establish safety, build resources.\sa180\par}
