\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 WHEN TO SEEK PROFESSIONAL HELP (Non-Emergency)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Consider professional support if:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Mental Health Concerns\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Depression lasting more than 2 weeks that significantly impairs functioning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Anxiety that prevents you from normal activities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Panic attacks occurring regularly (weekly or more)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trauma symptoms that are not improving with self-help approaches\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Thoughts of self-harm (even without intent)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Hearing or seeing things others do not\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Significant disruption to sleep, appetite, or concentration\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Relationship patterns that keep recurring despite your best efforts\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Substance/Behavioral Issues\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Inability to stop a behavior despite repeated attempts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Physical withdrawal symptoms when stopping\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Significant consequences (job loss, relationship damage, legal issues) without behavior change\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Using a substance or behavior to cope with daily life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Those close to you expressing concern\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 General Indicators\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You have tried the self-help approaches and are not improving\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You feel stuck in the same patterns despite effort\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Your level of distress is significantly impacting quality of life\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You do not trust yourself to stay safe\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 TYPES OF PROFESSIONALS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Psychiatrists (MD or DO)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Medical doctors who specialize in mental health\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can prescribe medication\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Best for: medication evaluation, complex conditions, when biology needs attention\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Psychologists (PhD, PsyD)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Doctoral-level training in psychology\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Provide therapy, testing, diagnosis\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Cannot prescribe medication (in most states/countries)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Best for: in-depth therapy, psychological testing, evidence-based treatment\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Licensed Therapists/Counselors (LMFT, LCSW, LPC, LMHC)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Master\u8217's-level mental health professionals\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Provide therapy and counseling\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Best for: general therapy, couples/family work, life transitions\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Addiction Specialists (CAC, CADC)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Specialize in substance use and behavioral addiction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Often work in treatment centers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Best for: addiction-specific treatment, recovery planning\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Peer Support/Recovery Coaches\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Not licensed clinicians but trained in recovery support\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Often have lived experience\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Best for: ongoing support, navigating recovery systems\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 HOW TO FIND A PROVIDER\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 1: Know What You Need\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Do you need medication? \u8594 ? Start with Psychiatrist or Primary Care\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Do you need therapy? \u8594 ? Therapist, Psychologist, Counselor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Is it addiction-specific? \u8594 ? Addiction Specialist or treatment program\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 2: Use Referral Resources\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Psychology Today Directory:} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.psychologytoday.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://www.psychologytoday.com/
}}}
 (filter by specialty, insurance, location)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Open Path Collective:} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://openpathcollective.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://openpathcollective.org/
}}}
 (low-cost therapy)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b SAMHSA Treatment Locator:} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://findtreatment.gov/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
https://findtreatment.gov/
}}}
 (US substance abuse/mental health)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Your Primary Care Doctor:} Can provide referrals\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Insurance Provider Directory:} Check your specific plan\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 3: Contact and Assess Fit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Call 2-3 providers. Ask:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Do you have experience with [your issue]?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"What is your approach?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab \u8220"Do you have availability?\u8221"\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Trust your gut. The relationship matters as much as the method.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Step 4: If Cost Is a Barrier\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Community mental health centers (sliding scale fees)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Training clinics at universities (low-cost but supervised quality)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Support groups (AA, NA, SMART Recovery\u8212-free)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Online therapy platforms (often cheaper than in-person)\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 12-STEP AND SUPPORT GROUPS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 These are free, widely available, and often lifesaving:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Alcoholics Anonymous (AA):} <www.aa.org>\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Narcotics Anonymous (NA):} <www.na.org>\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b SMART Recovery:} <www.smartrecovery.org> (evidence-based alternative to 12-step)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Refuge Recovery / Recovery Dharma:} Buddhist-based recovery programs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Al-Anon / Nar-Anon:} For family members of addicts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Codependents Anonymous (CoDA):} <www.coda.org>\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Adult Children of Alcoholics (ACA):} <www.adultchildren.org>\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 A NOTE ON MEDICATION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is no shame in medication.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If your brain chemistry is compromised\u8212-if you are struggling with severe depression, anxiety, ADHD, bipolar disorder, or psychosis\u8212-medication may be necessary to stabilize the system enough for therapy and self-help to work.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Medication is not:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A character flaw\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A sign you failed at self-help\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A life sentence (many people use it temporarily)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Medication is:}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab A tool\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sometimes necessary\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Something to discuss honestly with a prescriber\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Work with a psychiatrist or knowledgeable physician. Monitor side effects. Adjust as needed.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 WHEN THE OPERATOR IS OVERWHELMED\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is a point at which self-command reaches its limits.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the Passenger has taken the bridge and you cannot regain control\u8212-if the thoughts are too loud, the urges too strong, the despair too deep\u8212-{\b this is not failure. This is the signal to bring in reinforcements.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You are still the captain. Calling for help is a command decision.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b \u8220"Mayday, Mayday, Mayday. This is [Your Name]. Requesting assistance. I cannot manage alone.\u8221"}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That is not weakness. That is exactly what a good captain does.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
