{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b (TERMS & DEFINITIONS)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Quick reference for all naval and psychological terminology used in this manual.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 CORE FRAMEWORK\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Passenger}\line The limbic system / System 1. The older, emotionally-driven, survival-focused part of the brain. Automatic, fast, energy-efficient. Steers when you are on autopilot.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Operator}\line The prefrontal cortex / System 2. The newer, rational, planning-focused part of the brain. Deliberate, slow, energy-expensive. Responsible for long-term thinking and self-control.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Bridge}\line Your environment\u8212-the physical space where you live and work. Also refers to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "#chapter-9-the-bridge"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Chapter 9
}}}
 specifically.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Fleet}\line Your social network and relationships.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Bridge Crew}\line Your 2-5 closest allies who know your mission and actively support you.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Anchors}\line People who drain your energy, undermine your goals, or consistently make you feel worse.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Red Book}\line A physical notebook used for daily logging, self-observation, and pattern recognition.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 PSYCHOLOGICAL TERMS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b System 1 / System 2}\line From Daniel Kahneman\u8217's research. System 1 is fast, automatic, intuitive. System 2 is slow, deliberate, logical.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Ego Depletion / Decision Fatigue}\line The phenomenon where willpower diminishes with use, leaving the Passenger in control by day\u8217's end.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Default Mode Network (DMN)}\line Brain network active during daydreaming, rumination, and self-referential thinking. Often associated with the Passenger\u8217's running commentary.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Cognitive Dissonance}\line The discomfort of holding two contradictory beliefs or acting against your values.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Limerence}\line Intense, obsessive romantic attraction. The neurochemical \u8220"falling in love\u8221" phase.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Attachment Theory}\line Psychological framework describing how early relationships shape adult relationship patterns. Four styles: Secure, Anxious, Avoidant, Disorganized.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Window of Tolerance}\line The zone in which your nervous system can function effectively. Above it: hyperarousal. Below it: hypoarousal.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Abstinence Violation Effect (AVE)}\line The tendency for a small slip to cascade into a full relapse due to all-or-nothing thinking.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 NEUROCHEMICALS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Dopamine}\line The \u8220"pursuit\u8221" molecule. Associated with motivation, reward-seeking, and pleasure anticipation. Fires on {\i wanting}, not {\i having}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Cortisol}\line The stress hormone. Prepares the body for fight or flight. Chronic elevation impairs the Operator.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Adrenaline (Epinephrine)}\line Acute stress hormone. Triggers increased heart rate, alertness, and physical readiness.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Oxytocin}\line The bonding hormone. Released during intimacy, social connection, and trust.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Serotonin}\line Associated with mood, well-being, and calm. Notably {\i decreases} during limerence.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b BDNF (Brain-Derived Neurotrophic Factor)}\line A protein released during exercise that supports neuroplasticity and brain health. \u8220"Miracle-Gro for the brain.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 BRAIN STRUCTURES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Prefrontal Cortex (PFC)}\line Front of the brain. Seat of the Operator. Responsible for executive function, planning, and impulse control.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Limbic System}\line Older brain structures including the amygdala. Seat of emotion, memory, and survival instincts.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Amygdala}\line Almond-shaped structures in the temporal lobes. The brain\u8217's alarm system. Detects threats and triggers the stress response.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b HPA Axis}\line Hypothalamic-Pituitary-Adrenal Axis. The hormonal cascade that triggers the stress response.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Glymphatic System}\line The brain\u8217's waste-clearing system, active during deep sleep.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 PROTOCOLS & TECHNIQUES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Mutiny}\line When the Passenger seizes control from the Operator, typically through comfort scripts and emotional hijacking.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Standing Orders}\line Non-negotiable personal principles that are not up for daily debate.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Morning Watch}\line The daily morning log entry: Primary Objective, Threat Assessment, Passenger Alert.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Evening Debrief}\line The daily evening log entry: The Win, The Variance, Tomorrow\u8217's Anchor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b H.A.L.T.}\line Hungry, Angry, Lonely, Tired. A quick diagnostic for vulnerability.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b SITREP Drill}\line Stop, Inhale, Tension (release), Report, Execute, Proceed. A protocol for regulating in high-stress moments.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Box Breathing}\line Inhale 4 seconds, Hold 4 seconds, Exhale 4 seconds, Hold 4 seconds.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b 5-4-3-2-1 Grounding}\line Name 5 things you see, 4 you touch, 3 you hear, 2 you smell, 1 you taste. Sensory grounding technique for panic.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Dopamine Recalibration}\line Intentional reduction of high-dopamine stimuli to re-sensitize reward circuits.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Urge Surfing}\line Observing an urge without acting on it, allowing it to peak and pass.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Friction Principle}\line Reduce friction for good behaviors; increase friction for bad behaviors.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 SCRIPTS (Passenger Tactics)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Reward Script}\line \u8220"I deserve this. I\u8217've earned a treat.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Tomorrow Script}\line \u8220"I\u8217'll start tomorrow. I\u8217'm too tired tonight.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Fatalist Script}\line \u8220"I already blew it. Might as well keep going.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Imposter Script}\line \u8220"Who do I think I am? People like me don\u8217't succeed.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 METAPHORS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Drift}\line When the Passenger is steering unconsciously. Autopilot mode.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Void}\line Intentional silence and stillness. Where the Operator enters to recalibrate.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Reactor Core}\line A personal creative project that generates meaning and agency.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Freedom Fund}\line Savings buffer (1-6 months of expenses) that provides psychological security.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b The Shame Spiral}\line A cycle where shame triggers the behavior that caused the shame.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b MEDEVAC}\line Knowing when to seek professional help.\par}
